FORMAT: 1A
HOST: https://app.auvo.com.br/api/v1.0

# Auvo API V1.0

Auvo API provides a representation of the data found in your account at [Auvo](https://app.auvo.com.br).
We follow **REST** principles, so the API is stateless and http methods and response codes are used whenever possible.

The url for the requests is: `https://app.auvo.com.br/api/v1.0`

## Authentication

Every request **must** contain within it a data that provides `API key` and `Token`.
For `GET` and `DELETE` requests the data must be send in the query string and for `POST` and `PUT` the data **must** be send within the request body. 
`API key` and `Token` can be found by accesing [Menu > Integração](https://app.auvo.com.br/integracao/) in your Auvo's account

## Media Types
This API use JSON format to represent resources. When sending content on `PUT`/`POST` requests, you **must** specify the follow header:

    Content-Type: application/json

## Response Codes
The common [HTTP Response Status Codes](https://github.com/for-GET/know-your-http-well/blob/master/status-codes.md) are used.

You will often see:

* 200 (OK) - GET and PUT methods
* 201 (Created) - POST methods
* 204 (No content) - DELETE methods.

## Error States

When something goes wrong, the response status code can be `4xx` if the error is related to your request structure or `5xx` if it's our server's fault.

Example:

* 400 (Bad request) - GET /tasks?appKey=1, when token must be informed
* 404 (Not found) - GET /tasks/999?appKey=1&token=1, when the id 999 does not exist
* 415 (Unsupported media type) - POST /tasks, when the Content-Type header is not defined
* 500 (Internal server error) - When a request throws an unexpected error. If you see this status code, please contact us: help@auvo.com.br

# Group Users

## User [/users/{id}?appkey={appKey}&token={token}]
    
 A single `User` object.

+ Parameters

    + id (number) ... `userId` attribute of the `User`.

+ Model

    + Body
    
            {
                "userId": 123,
                "name": "Jason",
                "smartphoneNumber": "555555555555",
                "culture": "pt-BR",
                "jobPosition": "Administrador",
                "userType": { "userTypeId": 1, "description": "user" },
                "workDaysOfWeek": [ 
                    { "dayId": 1, "description": "sunday" },
                    { "dayId": 2, "description": "monday" },
                    { "dayId": 3, "description": "tuesday" },
                    { "dayId": 4, "description": "wednesday" },
                    { "dayId": 5, "description": "thursday" },
                    { "dayId": 6, "description": "friday" },
                    { "dayId": 7, "description": "saturday" }
                ],
                "startWorkHour": "08:00:00",
                "endWorkHour": "18:00:00",
                "startLunchHour": "12:00:00",
                "endLunchHour": "14:00:00",
                "hourValue": 0,
                "pictureBase64": "",
                "BasePoint": {
                  "address": "Rua C-137",
                  "latitude": -16.711903488917,
                  "longitude": -49.2775752032046
                },
                "openTaskInPlace": true,
                "grabGalleryPhotos": true,
                "gpsFrequency": 300
            }            

### Retrieve a User [GET]

+ Parameters
    + appKey (string) ... `appKey` of your Auvo's account
    + token (string) ... `token` of your Auvo's account

+ Response 200

    [User][]

+ Response 400

    When making a request with invalid options, status code 400 will be returned. For example, passing an invalid `token` parameter.

    + Body
    
            [
              {
                "errorCode": 4,
                "message": "Invalid token."
              }
            ]

+ Response 404
    
    When the resource with the specified id does not exist.
    
    + Body

### Add a new User [POST /users/]

The body example describes the minimum required attributes to successfully add an user. See the **Atributes** or **Json Schema** in the Example section for all allowed attributes.

+ Attributes
    + appKey (required, string) - appKey of the account
    + token (required, string) - token of the account
    + name (required, string) - name of the user
    + password (required, string) - password of the user
    + smartPhoneNumber (required, string) - user phone number(used as login). Only numbers
    + userType (required, number) - 1 - user | 2 - team manager | 3 - administrator
    + jobPosition (required, string) - job position of the user
    + culture (required, string) - culture name. For example `en-US`
    + hourValue (number) - Monetary value of the worked hour
    + endLunchHour (string) - "HH:mm:ss" 24 hours format
    + endWorkHour (string) - "HH:mm:ss" 24 hours format
    + startLunchHour (string) - "HH:mm:ss" 24 hours format
    + startWorkHour (string) - "HH:mm:ss" 24 hours format
    + workDaysOfWeek (array[number]) - 1 - Sunday | 2  -Monday | 3 - Tuesday | 4 - Wednesday | 5 - Thuersday | 6 - Friday | 7 - Sunday
    + address (string) - base point address
    + latitude (number) - base point latitude
    + longitude (number) - base point longitude
    + openTaskInPlace (boolean) - open in-place task by application
    * grabGalleryPhotos (boolean) - allows you to take gallery photo in the app
    + gpsFrequency (number) - 60 - 1 minute| 120 - 2 minutes |180 - 3 minutes | 240 - 4 minutes | 300 - 5 minutes

+ Request (application/json)

    + Body 
        
            {
                "appKey": "appKey of the account",
                "token": "token of the account",
                "name": "Jack",
                "password": "MyPassword",
                "smartPhoneNumber": "555555555555",
                "userType": 1,
                "culture": "pt-BR",
            }

    + Schema
    
            {
                "appKey": string,
                "token": string,
                "name": string,
                "password": string,
                "smartPhoneNumber": string,
                "userType": integer,
                "jobPosition": [string],
                "culture": string,
                "hourValue": [integer],
                "endLunchHour": ["HH:mm:ss"],
                "endWorkHour": ["HH:mm:ss"],
                "startLunchHour": ["HH:mm:ss"],
                "startWorkHour": ["HH:mm:ss"],
                "workDaysOfWeek": [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7]
            }

+ Response 201

    + Header
    
            Location: https://auvo.com.com.br/v1.0/users/23

    + Body
    
            {
                "userId": 23,
                "name": "Jack",
                "smartphoneNumber": "555555555555",
                "culture": "pt-BR",
                "jobPosition": "",
                "userType": { "userTypeId": 1, "description": "user" },
                "workDaysOfWeek": [],
                "startWorkHour": "",
                "endWorkHour": "",
                "startLunchHour": "",
                "endLunchHour": ",
                "hourValue": 0,
                "pictureBase64": "",
                "BasePoint": {
                  "address": "",
                  "latitude": 0,
                  "longitude": 0
                },
                "openTaskInPlace": true,
                "grabGalleryPhotos": true,
                "gpsFrequency": 300
            }

### Edit a User [PUT /users/{id}]
To update a `User`, send a JSON with updated value for one or more of the `User` attributes. All attributes values (states) from the previous version of this `User` are carried over by default if not included in the hash. See the **Atributes** or **Json Schema** in the Example section for all allowed attributes.

+ Attributes
    + appKey (required, string) - appKey of the account
    + token (required, string) - token of the account
    + name (string) - new name of the user
    + password (string) - new password of the user
    + userType (number) - 1 - user | 2 - manager | 3 - administrator
    + jobPosition (string) - new job position of the user
    + culture (string) - culture name. For example `en-US`
    + hourValue (number) - Monetary value of the worked hour
    + endLunchHour (string) - "HH:mm:ss" 24 hours format
    + endWorkHour (string) - "HH:mm:ss" 24 hours format
    + startLunchHour (string) - "HH:mm:ss" 24 hours format
    + startWorkHour (string) - "HH:mm:ss" 24 hours format
    + workDaysOfWeek (array[number]) - 1 - Sunday | 2  -Monday | 3 - Tuesday | 4 - Wednesday | 5 - Thuersday | 6 - Friday | 7 - Sunday
    + address (string) - base point address
    + latitude (number) - base point latitude
    + longitude (number) - base point longitude
    + openTaskPlace (boolean) - open in-place task by application
    * grabGalleryPhotos (boolean) - allows you to take gallery photo in the app
    + gpsFrequency (number) - 60 - 1 minute| 120 - 2 minutes |180 - 3 minutes | 240 - 4 minutes | 300 - 5 minutes

+ Request (application/json)


    + Body

            {
                "appKey": "appKey of the account"
                "token": "token of the account",
                "name": "New person name"
            }

    + Schema

            {
                "appKey": string,
                "token": string,
                "name": [string],
                "password": [string],
                "userType": [integer],
                "jobPosition": [string],
                "culture": [string],
                "hourValue": [integer],
                "endLunchHour": ["HH:mm:ss"],
                "endWorkHour": ["HH:mm:ss"],
                "startLunchHour": ["HH:mm:ss"],
                "startWorkHour": ["HH:mm:ss"],
                "workDaysOfWeek": [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7]
            }

+ Response 200
    
    + Body
    
            {
                "userId": 23,
                "name": "New person name",
                "smartphoneNumber": "555555555555",
                "culture": "pt-BR",
                "jobPosition": "Administrador",
                "userType": { "userTypeId": 1, "description": "user" },
                "workDaysOfWeek": [ 
                    { "dayId": 1, "description": "sunday" },
                    { "dayId": 2, "description": "monday" },
                    { "dayId": 3, "description": "tuesday" },
                    { "dayId": 4, "description": "wednesday" },
                    { "dayId": 5, "description": "thursday" },
                    { "dayId": 6, "description": "friday" },
                    { "dayId": 7, "description": "saturday" }
                ],
                "startWorkHour": "08:00:00",
                "endWorkHour": "18:00:00",
                "startLunchHour": "12:00:00",
                "endLunchHour": "14:00:00",
                "hourValue": 0,
                "pictureBase64": "",
                "BasePoint": {
                  "address": "Rua C-137",
                  "latitude": -16.711903488917,
                  "longitude": -16.711903488917
                },
                "openTaskInPlace": true,
                "grabGalleryPhotos": true,
                "gpsFrequency": 300
            }    
            


