### Retrieve a Task [GET]

+ Parameters
    + appKey (string) ... `appKey` of your Auvo's account.
    + token (string) ... `token` of your Auvo's account.

+ Response 200

    [Task][]

+ Response 400

    When making a request with invalid options, status code 400 will be returned. For example, passing an invalid `appKey` parameter.

    + Body
    
            [
              {
                "errorCode": 4,
                "message": "Invalid appKey."
              }
            ]

+ Response 404
    
    When the resource with the specified id does not exist.
    
    + Body

### Add a new Task [POST /tasks/]

The body example describes the minimum required attributes to successfully add a task. See the **Atributes** or **Json Schema** in the Example section for all allowed attributes.

+ Attributes
    + appKey (required, string) - appKey of your Auvo's account
    + token (required, string) - token of your Auvo's account
    + idUserFrom (required, number) - userId of the User that is opening the task
    + idUserTo (required, number) - userId of the User responsable for executing the task
    + taskDate (required, string) - date and time for the execution of the task
    + localDate (required, string) - local date and time of the creation of the task
    + address (required, string) - address of the task
    + orientation (required, string) - orientation of the task
    + priority (required, number) - priority of the task. 1 - Low | 2 - Medium | 3 - High
    + latitude (number) - latitude of the task
    + longitude (number) - longitude of the task
    + checkListId (number) - checkListId of the CheckList included in the task
    + customerId (number) - customerId of the Customer chosen for the task
    + checkinManual (boolean)
    + taskType (number) - taskTypeId of the task type
    + attachments (array) - list of attachment object, this object MUST have "name" and "file" attributes, the name MUST contain the file type (Ex. "my_file.pdf")
+ Request (application/json)

    + Body 
        
            {
                "appKey": "appKey of the account",
                "token": "token of the account",
                "idUserFrom": 99,
                "idUserTo": 69,
                "taskDate": "2016-04-23T18:00:00",
                "localDate": "2016-04-23T08:00:00",
                "latitude": -16.6872086111083,
                "longitude": -49.2995542287827,
                "address": "avenue Y",
                "orientation": "Gotta Catch 'Em All",
                "priority": 1,
                "taskType": 3,
                "attachments": [
                    {
                        "name": "my_file.pdf",
                        "file": "base64 encoded file"
                    }
                ]
            }

    + Schema
    
            {
                "appKey": string,
                "token": string,
                "idUserFrom": integer,
                "idUserTo": integer,
                "taskDate": "yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ss",
                "localDate": "yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ss",
                "latitude": integer,
                "longitude": integer,
                "address": string,
                "orientation": string,
                "priority": integer,
                "checkListId": integer,
                "customerId": integer
                "checkinManual": boolean,
                "attachments": array
            }

+ Response 201

    + Header
    
            Location: https://auvo.com.com.br/v1.0/tasks/100

    + Body
    
            {
                "taskId": 100,
                "idUserFrom": 99,
                "idUserTo": 69,
                "creationDate": "2016-04-23T08:00:00",
                "taskDate": "2016-04-23T18:00:00",
                "latitude": -16.6872086111083,
                "longitude": -49.2995542287827,
                "address": "avenue Y",
                "orientation": "Gotta Catch 'Em All",
                "priority": 1,
                "deliveredOnSmarthPhone": false,
                "deliveredDate": "",
                "finished": false,
                "report": "",
                "visualized": false,
                "visualizedDate": "",
                "checkIn": false,
                "checkInDate": "",
                "checkOut": false,
                "checkOutDate": "",
                "checkinManual": false,
                "signatureBase64": "",
                "attachmentsBase64": [],
                "signatureUrl": "",
                "attachmentsUrl": [],
                "checkList": []
            }

### Edit a Task [PUT /tasks/{id}]
To update a `Task`, send a JSON with updated value for one or more of the `Task` attributes. All attributes values (states) from the previous version of this `Task` are carried over by default if not included in the hash. See the **Atributes** or **Json Schema** in the Example section for all allowed attributes.

+ Attributes
    + appKey (required, string) - appKey of the account
    + token (required, string) - token of the account
    + taskDate (string) - new date for the task
    + orientation (string) - new orientation for the task
    + priority (number) - new priority for the task. 1 - Low | 2 - Medium | 3 - High
    + checkListCode (number) - new checklist for the task 
    + closeTask (boolean) - new status of the task. Send true to close the task
    + checkinManual (boolean)
    + idUserTo (number) - new user to for the task
    + taskType (number) - taskTypeId of the task type
    + attachments (array) - list of attachment object, this attribute will only insert new attachments to the task
    + removeAllAttachmentsInsertedByMe (boolean) - this option will remove all the previous attachments inserted by the requester in the task
+ Request (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                "appKey": "appKey of the account"
                "token": "token of the account",
                "closeTask": true,
                "removeAllAttachmentsInsertedByMe": false
            }

    + Schema

            {
                "appKey": string,
                "token": string,
                "taskDate": ["yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ss"],
                "orientation": [string],
                "priority": [number],
                "checkListCode": [number],
                "closeTask": [boolean]
            }

+ Response 200
    
    + Body
    
            {
                "taskId": 32,
                "idUserFrom": 321,
                "idUserTo": 321,
                "creationDate": "2016-03-23T08:00:35",
                "taskDate": "2016-03-23T14:00:00",
                "latitude": -16.6872086111083,
                "longitude": -49.2995542287827,
                "address": "avenue X",
                "orientation": "Work!",
                "priority": "1",
                "deliveredOnSmarthPhone": true,
                "deliveredDate": "2016-03-23T08:11:31",
                "finished": true,
                "report": "",
                "visualized": false,
                "visualizedDate": "",
                "checkIn": false,
                "checkInDate": "",
                "checkinManual": false,
                "checkOut": false,
                "checkOutDate": "",
                "signatureBase64": "",
                "attachmentsBase64": [],
                "checkList": []
            }


### Delete a Task [DELETE]

+ Parameters

