# Group Customers

## Customer [/customers/{id}?appkey={appKey}&token={token}]
    
 A single `Customer` object.

+ Parameters

    + id (number) ... `customerId` attribute of the `Customer`.

+ Model

    + Body
    
            {
                "customerId": 42,
                "name": "Terêscio",
                "cpfCnpj": "90614997000162",
                "phoneNumber": "5566123123",
                "email": "terenscio@customer.com",
                "manager": "Oristides",
                "managerJobPosition": "Manager",
                "note": "nothing to say",
                "address": "lake yululu",
                "latitude": -16.6872086111083,
                "longitude": -49.2995542287827,
                "segmentId": 1
            }

### Retrieve a Customer [GET]

+ Parameters
    + appKey (string) ... `appKey` of your Auvo's account.
    + token (string) ... `token` of your Auvo's account.

+ Response 200

    [Customer][]

+ Response 400

    When making a request with invalid options, status code 400 will be returned. For example, passing an invalid `appKey` parameter.

    + Body
    
            [
              {
                "errorCode": 4,
                "message": "Invalid appKey."
              }
            ]

+ Response 404
    
    When the resource with the specified id does not exist.
    
    + Body

### Add a new Customer [POST /customers/]

The body example describes the minimum required attributes to successfully add a customer. See the **Atributes** or **Json Schema** in the Example section for all allowed attributes.

+ Attributes
    + appKey (required, string) - appKey of your Auvo's account
    + token (required, string) - token of your Auvo's account
    + name (required, string) - customer name
    + address (required, string) - customer address
    + latitude (string) - latitude of the customer address
    + longitude (string) - longitude of the customer address
    + phoneNumber (string) - customer phone number
    + email (string) - customer contect email
    + manager (string) - customer manager
    + managerJobPosition (string) - job position of the customer manager
    + note (string) - note about the customer
    + cpfCnpj (string) - customer CPF/CNPJ
    + segmentId (number) - id of a registered segment

+ Request (application/json)

    + Body 
        
            {
                "appKey": "appKey of the account",
                "token": "token of the account",
                "name": "Acme",
                "cpfCnpj": "90614997000162",
                "address": "Bermuda triangle",
                "latitude": 32.294388,
                "longitude": -64.773502,
                "phoneNumber": "5562123123123"
            }

    + Schema
    
            {
                "appKey": string,
                "token": string,
                "name": string,
                "cpfCnpj":string,
                "address": string,
                "latitude": number,
                "longitude": number,
                "phoneNumber": [string],
                "email": [string],
                "manager": [string],
                "managerJobPosition": [string],
                "note": [string],
                "segmentId": [number]
            }

+ Response 201

    + Header
    
            Location: https://auvo.com.com.br/v1.0/customers/1024

    + Body
    
            {
                "customerId": 57,
                "name": "Acme",
                "cpfCnpj": "90614997000162",
                "phoneNumber": "",
                "email": "",
                "manager": "",
                "managerJobPosition": "",
                "note": "",
                "address": "Bermuda triangle",
                "latitude": 32.294388,
                "longitude": -64.773502,
                "segmentId": 0
            }

### Edit a Customer [PUT /customers/{id}]
To update a `Customer`, send a JSON with updated value for one or more of the `Customer` attributes. All attributes values (states) from the previous version of this `Customer` are carried over by default if not included in the hash. See the **Atributes** or **Json Schema** in the Example section for all allowed attributes.

+ Attributes
    + appKey (required, string) - appKey of the account
    + token (required, string) - token of the account
    + name (string) - new customer name
    + address (string) - new customer address
    + latitude (string) - new latitude of the customer address
    + longitude (string) - new longitude of the customer address
    + phoneNumber (string) - new customer phone number
    + email (string) - new customer contect email
    + manager (string) - new customer manager
    + managerJobPosition (string) - new job position of the customer manager
    + note (string) - new note about the customer
    + cpfCnpj (string) - customer CPF/CNPJ
    + segmentId (number) - id of a registered segment

+ Request (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                "appKey": "appKey of the account"
                "token": "token of the account",
                "name": "new name"
            }

    + Schema

            {
                "appKey": string,
                "token": string,
                "name": [string],
                "cpfCnpj": string,
                "address": [string],
                "latitude": [number],
                "longitude": [number],
                "phoneNumber": [string],
                "email": [string],
                "manager": [string],
                "managerJobPosition": [string],
                "note": [string],
                "segmentId": [number]
            }

+ Response 200
    
    + Body
    
            {
                "customerId": 57,
                "name": "new name",
                "cpfCnpj": "90614997000162",
                "phoneNumber": "",
                "email": "",
                "manager": "",
                "managerJobPosition": "",
                "note": "",
                "address": "Bermuda triangle",
                "latitude": 32.294388,
                "longitude": -64.773502,
                "segmentId": 0
            }


### Delete a Customer [DELETE]

+ Parameters

    + appKey (string) ... `appKey` of your Auvo's account.
    + token (string) ... `token` of your Auvo's account.

+ Response 204

    When succeed, return 204 and an empty payload.

    + Body

